[SN]TITLE[SN]
Jersey man killed in Val d'Isere skiing accident

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man from Jersey has died in a skiing accident in the French Alps.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mark Le Sueur, 57, known to many as Frank, was skiing off-piste near Val d'Isere, according to French police at the resort.
Mr Le Sueur, from Trinity, died whilst being airlifted by helicopter to hospital in Grenoble.
The UK Foreign Office said it had been in contact with local authorities and was ready to provide support to his family.
